main event: A possible satellite or unidentified object was observed in the sky at coordinates 35-40N 175-15W on 2 Aug 64 at 1422Z.
interesting points: The object was described as bright, similar to a first magnitude star.
The object was observed moving in an eastward direction.
The duration and type of the observation is unknown.
No evaluation or conclusion about the identity of the object was provided.
The report was part of the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book, which investigated UFO sightings.
